	(248,41,'_sponsors','field_5827799a9ceeb'),
	(249,41,'tldr','<blockquote><strong>Please register your team at the following <a title=\"Battlefy\" href=\"https://battlefy.com/mad-city/mad-city-lan-2-with-wit-gaming/5716c1b3c3f0d37d12e0b8ae\">Battlefy</a> link if you intend on participating.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>Assuming there are 18 teams, we will be promising everyone a minimum of 5 games. You can come to the tournament, lose every single match, and still play 5 games total.</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>On the evening of Friday May 27th, we will have a live stream on our twitch channel (<a title=\"twitch.tv/madcitygg\" href=\"http://twitch.tv/madcitygg\">http://twitch.tv/madcitygg</a>) to randomize the group seeding before the event. If we\'re able to book all 18 teams in advance, we can announce the arrival times of all teams participating. But until then, plan on being there <strong>NO LATER than 10am on May 29th to secure your spot at the event</strong>. We are going to have pretty strict disqualification rules in place for teams we can\'t find.</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>As mentioned, signing up with 3 players reserves your teams spot, however I strongly suggest coordinating with all of your teammates and signing up together.</blockquote>'),
